{
    "chapter": 82,
    "verses": {
        "1": {
            "verses": {
                "82:1": {
                    "id": 1
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>When the heaven is split open, [when it is] rent asunder,</h2>"
        },
        "2": {
            "verses": {
                "82:2": {
                    "id": 2
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and when the stars are dispersed, [when] they expire and begin to fall,</p>"
        },
        "3": {
            "verses": {
                "82:3": {
                    "id": 3
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and when the seas are burst forth, released one upon the other, forming one mass of water, so that the sweet [water] mixes with the salty;</p>"
        },
        "4": {
            "verses": {
                "82:4": {
                    "id": 4
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>and when the tombs are overturned, [when] their earth [above them] is dug up and its dead are raised (the response to idh, `when', and all that is supplemented thereto is [the following]):</h2>"
        },
        "5": {
            "verses": {
                "82:5": {
                    "id": 5
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>a soul, every soul, will know, at the time of the [occurrence of the] things mentioned, which is the Day of Resurrection, what it has sent ahead, in the way of deeds, and, what [it has], left behind, of these and did not do.</p>"
        },
        "6": {
            "verses": {
                "82:6": {
                    "id": 6
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>O, disbelieving, man! What has deceived you with regard to your generous Lord?, so that you have disobeyed Him,</p>"
        },
        "7": {
            "verses": {
                "82:7": {
                    "id": 7
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Who created you, when you were not, then made you upright, in your created form, with sound limbs, then proportioned you (read fa-`adalak or fa-`addalak), making you symmetrical in shape, with well-proportioned parts, so that no hand or leg is longer than the other,</p>"
        },
        "8": {
            "verses": {
                "82:8": {
                    "id": 8
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>assembling you in whatever (m is a relative) form He will?</h2>"
        },
        "9": {
            "verses": {
                "82:9": {
                    "id": 9
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>No indeed! — a deterrent against letting oneself be misled by the generosity of God, exalted be He. Rather you, that is, disbelievers of Mecca, deny Judgement, requital for deeds;</p>"
        },
        "10": {
            "verses": {
                "82:10": {
                    "id": 10
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Yet lo! there are above you watchers, from among the angels, over your deeds,</p>"
        },
        "11": {
            "verses": {
                "82:11": {
                    "id": 11
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>noble, in God's sight, writers, of these [deeds],</h2>"
        },
        "12": {
            "verses": {
                "82:12": {
                    "id": 12
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>who know whatever you do, all of it.</h2>"
        },
        "13": {
            "verses": {
                "82:13": {
                    "id": 13
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Indeed the pious, the believers who are sincere in their faith, shall be amid bliss, [in] Paradise,</p>"
        },
        "14": {
            "verses": {
                "82:14": {
                    "id": 14
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and indeed the profligates, the disbelievers, shall be in Hell-fire, a scorching fire,</p>"
        },
        "15": {
            "verses": {
                "82:15": {
                    "id": 15
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>entering it, to suffer its heat, on the Day of Judgement, [the Day of] Requital,</p>"
        },
        "16": {
            "verses": {
                "82:16": {
                    "id": 16
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and they shall not be absent from it, [they shall not] be taken out of it.</p>"
        },
        "17": {
            "verses": {
                "82:17": {
                    "id": 17
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>And what would show you, [what would] inform you, what the Day of Judgement is?</p>"
        },
        "18": {
            "verses": {
                "82:18": {
                    "id": 18
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Again, what would show you what the Day of Judgement is? — [repeated] to emphasise its enormity.</p>"
        },
        "19": {
            "verses": {
                "82:19": {
                    "id": 19
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>[It is] a day (read yawmu) when no soul will be of any avail, any use, to another soul, and the [absolute] command on that day will be God's: there will be no [power of] command for anyone other than Him thereat, in other words, none has been given the power to mediate thereupon, in contrast to [situations] in this world. Meccan or Medinese, consisting of 36 verses.</p>"
        }
    }
}